introduction: Trust no one, not even yourself.

vocabulary.definition: fancy or stylish in a pretentious or showy way
vocabulary.example: They are headed to some fancy schmancy sky base.

vocabulary.definition: heavily soaked with liquid or moisture; damp and wet
vocabulary.example: Hey, that waffle's in water, it's going to get real soggy.

vocabulary.definition: a person who engages in a pursuit, especially a sport, on an unpaid basis
vocabulary.example: I can already tell they're amateurs because they built a sky base near all this water.

vocabulary.definition: concerned with beauty or the appreciation of beauty
vocabulary.example: I'm not the biggest fan of this landscaping and these aesthetics.

vocabulary.definition: a phrase or opinion that is overused and betrays a lack of original thought
vocabulary.example: There are very few times where something so cliche is so beautiful.

vocabulary.definition: attempting to impress by affecting greater importance or merit than is actually possessed
vocabulary.example: The party was full of pretentious people showing off their expensive belongings.
